Sentencas: Ca3Co2O6 (CCO) cathode is synthesized by sol-gel method for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) on a new Sm0.075Nd0.075Ce0.85O2-delta (SNDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Ca3Co2O6 as cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure, micromorphology and electrochemical performance of CCO cathode with SNDC electrolyte are characterized.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Ca3Co2O6 as cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the CCO cathode calcined at 850 degrees C for 10 h can form single phase hexagonal crystal structure, and have good chemical compatibility with SNDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Ca3Co2O6 as cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The CCO cathode sintered at 850 degrees C for 3 h shows the best cathode performance, and the area specific resistances (ASR) of CCO cathode are found to be 0.427, 0.729 and 1.515 Omega cm(2) at 800, 750 and 700 degrees C, respectively, and the maximal power densities of SNDC electrolyte supported SOFC with CCO cathode reach 394.1, 295.1 and 194.6 mW cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Ca3Co2O6 as cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
